JX Nippon Oil and Energy Corp ,
 Japan â€™s biggest refiner, will build three solar power stations
in Japan.  The Tokyo-based company will build a 1-megawatt station in
Fukushima prefecture and a 4-megawatt plant in Akita, both in
northern Japan, it said in a statement today. No financial terms
were disclosed.  A 12-megawatt station will be set up in the southern
prefecture of Okinawa, according to the statement. The plants
will start operations by March 2015, according to JX Energy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
